-KIT: How do you feel?

37:46.197 --> 37:47.799
(exhales)

37:47.833 --> 37:51.403
Like I was just born.

37:51.437 --> 37:54.906
Like I'm the luckiest person
in the world.

37:54.940 --> 37:58.410
It's never been like this, ever,

37:58.444 --> 38:01.046
just breathing.

38:03.148 --> 38:04.916
My parents?

38:04.950 --> 38:06.452
Hey, Elo.

38:06.485 --> 38:08.253
CONRAD:
Your dad's procedure went great.

38:08.286 --> 38:11.122
Your mom...

38:11.156 --> 38:14.125
There were some complications
with the pulmonary artery.

38:14.159 --> 38:17.162
It can happen in difficult
surgeries like this.

38:17.195 --> 38:20.098
-Recovery's not gonna be easy.
-MINA: But...

38:20.131 --> 38:21.867
we believe she can make it.

38:21.900 --> 38:24.970
Oh... Mom.

38:36.147 --> 38:38.116
Mom, I'm here.

38:38.149 --> 38:43.154
Right here, where you've
always been: beside me,

38:43.188 --> 38:46.958
helping me.

38:46.992 --> 38:49.227
Mom, can you hear me?

39:06.177 --> 39:08.146
MINA:
You're famous.

39:08.179 --> 39:10.516
Just think how much more
insufferable you'll be.

39:10.549 --> 39:12.017
I wouldn't count on it.

39:12.050 --> 39:14.185
I have recently dined
on humble pie,

39:14.219 --> 39:16.488
and it's a flavor
I will not soon forget.

39:16.522 --> 39:19.057
That surgery was insane.

39:19.090 --> 39:21.059
I mean, we're all proud
of the work we did

39:21.092 --> 39:22.861
and are happy for Eloise
and her family,

39:22.894 --> 39:25.230
but that could have ended
very badly.

39:25.263 --> 39:27.065
A triple tragedy.

39:27.098 --> 39:30.035
Skill certainly played
a large part, but so did luck.

39:30.068 --> 39:33.171
-It was practically a miracle.
-(clears throat)

39:33.204 --> 39:36.074
Check it out. Our next surgery.

39:36.107 --> 39:38.376
What are you gonna do?

39:38.410 --> 39:40.912
Uh,are going
to perform a flawless

39:40.946 --> 39:43.048
aortic valve replacement.

39:43.081 --> 39:45.951
-With a QuoVadis valve?
-A-A QuoVadis valve? Excuse me?

39:45.984 --> 39:48.687
There are no QuoVadis valves
on Chastain shelves.

39:48.720 --> 39:50.589
-(sniffles)
-Are you telling me...

39:50.622 --> 39:52.057
-(chuckles)
-Bell pulled them?

39:52.090 --> 39:54.092
Every last one.

39:54.125 --> 39:57.095
We've got the old reliable
valves back for good.

39:57.128 --> 39:58.797
-Well, today is
truly miraculous.
-Mm.

39:58.830 --> 40:02.267
Bell, of all people,
did the right thing.

40:06.071 --> 40:09.040
You pulled the valves.
Are you insane?

40:09.074 --> 40:11.142
It was the right thing to do.

40:11.176 --> 40:14.780
And I believe, eventually,
you'll agree with my decision.

40:14.813 --> 40:16.582
This is way out of line.

40:16.615 --> 40:18.817
Obviously,
there will be consequences.

40:18.850 --> 40:20.852
You'll regret this, Dr. Bell.

40:29.495 --> 40:32.030
Long day.

40:34.833 --> 40:37.068
A great day.

40:37.102 --> 40:38.837
(knocking on door)

40:38.870 --> 40:40.438
I'm leaving, Dr. B. Uh, don't
forget you have that dinner

40:40.472 --> 40:42.474
with the CEO
of Atlanta General at 8:00.

40:42.508 --> 40:44.910
I canceled it. I have surgery.

40:44.943 --> 40:46.678
GRAYSON:
Ah, that's a nice change.

40:46.712 --> 40:49.380
See you tomorrow, boss.

40:52.618 --> 40:54.686
To you.

40:54.720 --> 40:58.490
Thank you for what you did.

41:01.059 --> 41:04.029
Thank you.

41:04.062 --> 41:06.064
Allow me.

41:18.910 --> 41:21.146
It's a good look.

41:21.179 --> 41:24.550
-Yeah, I just had it pressed.
-(chuckles softly)

41:26.151 --> 41:28.153
(line ringing)

41:31.189 --> 41:33.124
(over phone):
You've reached Mark Truscott,

41:33.158 --> 41:35.293
Director of the Center
of Devices at the FDA.

41:35.326 --> 41:37.128
Leave a message.

41:37.162 --> 41:38.530
